@3000 = ~Hey there, friends! You are friends, right? You wanted to know where the nastiest poison comes from, didn’t you? Well—lucky you! I've got a map right here. It shows the spot where I usually meet the fella who brews the real stuff. But, listen—just a word of advice, friend to friend: don’t mess around with that guy—smile at him wrong, and you’ll be coughing blood.~
@3001 = ~Where's my map? I’m feeling kinda dizzy all of a sudden. Think I’ll head to the tavern, get something strong to clear my head.~
@3002 = ~Anyway... here's the map. Farewell for now. I’m feeling kinda dizzy all of a sudden. Think I’ll head to the tavern, get something strong to clear my head.~
@3003 = ~Well now, what do we have here? You lookin’ for something that makes problems disappear... real quiet-like? I’ve got potions, powders, and little drips of doom—if your coin’s honest and your conscience ain’t too fussy.~
@3004 = ~That does sound interesting. What exactly are you offering?~
@3005 = ~I’m not ready to deal just yet.~
@3006 = ~Oh, it's you again! What do you want? I’ve got potions, powders, and little drips of doom—if your coin’s honest and your conscience ain’t too fussy.~
@3007 = ~You disgust me. The world needs less filth like you!~
@3008 = ~Tell me where you get the real good stuff from.~
@3009 = ~Oh, a bit of this and that—venoms to silence a snitch, brews to slow a soldier, drops that’ll send a man coughing up his liver. Handy little tools to make your life easier... and theirs shorter.~
@3010 = ~You're a blight on this city—I should end you right here!~
@3011 = ~I’m looking for something truly powerful.~
@3012 = ~Not now. I need to think it through.~
@3013 = ~Truth is, I don’t keep the real nasty stuff on me—too many pryin’ eyes, you feel me? But... for the right coin and the right kind of customer, I might know a bloke who knows a bloke who delivers the deadliest poison you’ve ever seen!~
@3014 = ~Someone like you has no right to draw breath. Prepare to die!~
@3015 = ~I'm looking for the person who makes your deadliest poison.~
@3016 = ~This isn't the right moment. I'll be back.~
@3017 = ~Ha! You think I’d spill my supplier to the first smooth-talker with a pouch full of coins? Get real. That kind of info don’t come free—and even if it did, I ain’t riskin’ my neck for a stranger in boots too clean for this part of town. Who do you think you are?~
@3018 = ~You’ll need more than words to get me talking!~
@3019 = ~Please, just tell me.~
@3020 = ~How much did you say the price was again?~
@3021 = ~Everyone has a price. What’s yours?~
@3022 = ~My strength isn’t for show. Do I really have to beat the answer out of you? Choose wisely which side of my fists you’d like to be on.~
@3023 = ~Minsc, perhaps Skann would feel more cooperative if you showed him your muscles. Would you be so kind?~
@3024 = ~I'm <CHARNAME>. People call me notorious. Ask around what happens to those who cross me.~
@3025 = ~I killed Maevar. So unless you want to follow him, you’ll start talking.~
@3026 = ~You might have heard of me— I'm <CHARNAME>. I've brought down worse than you, and I don't need poison to do it. So tell me what I want to know!~
@3027 = ~I work for the Shadow Thieves. I doubt they'd be pleased to hear about your little side business.~
@3028 = ~Ever heard of that new guild—the one that drains the blood from their enemies? I doubt your poisons would do them much harm. And, well... I work for them.~
@3029 = ~I don’t deal with back-alley scum like you!~
@3030 = ~I’ll return when the time’s right.~
@3031 = ~That's a hamster. You're threatening me with a rodent?~
@3032 = ~Take your circus act and scram—unless you’ve got gold in your hand or steel at my throat. I’ve got a reputation to keep!~
@3033 = ~Oh, Minsc... I don’t think he understood Boo’s warning.~
@3034 = ~Maybe keep the hamster in reserve until we’ve mastered the art of intimidation.~
@3035 = ~Perhaps we ought to rehearse that little act before attempting it again.~
@3036 = ~A valiant effort... but perhaps best refined before an encore.~
@3037 = ~A bold attempt. Still, timing and delivery are everything.~
@3038 = ~That certainly didn’t go as planned. Next time, try cruelty paired with intelligence.~
@3039 = ~Showin' off muscles? I’d rather show him his own bowels spillin’ out. That gets the chatter started, I tell ya!~
@3040 = ~Hah... If I told you, I’d be a dead man by dawn...~
@3041 = ~Thinkin’ again... safety’s not exactly my strong suit these days. Maybe it’s time to finally head south, eh? Thing is, passage to Calimshan — real ship, real fast — that don’t come cheap. And settin’ up in Calimport? Let’s just say I’ll need a little help gettin’ back on my feet. So if you’re real keen on supportin’ my fresh start... let’s say ten thousand gold.~
@3042 = ~For ten thousand gold, I vanish from this cursed city. For ten thousand gold, I’ll forget I ever knew my supplier—and you’ll know everything I do. Deal?~
@3043 = ~Very well. Here is your money.~
@3044 = ~That is too much.~
@3045 = ~I don't have that much money.~
@3046 = ~Well then—hand over the coins! I don’t know if you’re just mad or plain stupid, payin’ that much for a scrap of info. Not that I care. Soon I’ll be livin’ like a pasha in Calimport!~
@3047 = ~Oh, it's you? Now that you mention it—folks been whispering about some notorious <PRO_RACE> like you from the North, stirring up trouble in the city...~
@3048 = ~Yep, that's me.~
@3049 = ~Trouble is what I do best.~
@3050 = ~I’m not here to cause trouble. I’m here to end it.~
@3051 = ~Oh—you’re with the Shadow Thieves? Tell them that I... uh... look, I never meant to step on anyone’s turf.~
@3052 = ~Name your supplier and we’ll call it even.~
@3053 = ~Ah... that new guild. Yeah, I’ve heard stories—nasty ones. They tore my buddy Therrik to bits!~
@3054 = ~Yeah, poor Therrik. Screamed like a stuck pig. Probably would've preferred your poison.~
@3055 = ~You consider Therrik's fate bad? There's even worse for those who do not cooperate.~
@3056 = ~Before he died, Therrik told my masters about you.~
@3057 = ~Hey, I don’t want no trouble, right? I—I’m just running a bit of a business here...~
@3058 = ~You’re lookin’ for the one behind the real nasty poison? Sure. He’s got a name... and probably more blood on his hands than most!~
@3059 = ~His name’s Delgorth. Weird fellow. I’ve only met him twice—in a glade out in the wood. That’s all I know of him, swear on the gutter gods. I'll give you his particulars.~
@3060 = ~Smart choice.~
@3061 = ~That’s all I needed.~
@3062 = ~The map’ll get you there. Thing’s burnin’ a hole in my pocket anyway. Here—your problem now, not mine anymore.~
@3063 = ~We’re done here. Pleasure doin’ business... sort of! If anyone asks — we never spoke. Time for me to vanish.~
@3064 = ~Well, ain’t you the hero type. Shame you picked the wrong roof to play vigilante on! Let’s fight, then! My little friends, to me!~
@3065 = ~Fine, fine. Come back if you grow a taste for shadows and want your troubles bottled. I'll be here... till I ain't.~
@3066 = ~Pah! You won’t get anything from me unless you got something really good to offer. Get lost!~
@3067 = ~Hey, you in the back—what was your name again? <CHARNAME>? You can come collect your dying friend! And tell his masters: Never cross a Malagent!~
@3068 = ~<CHARNAME>! We’re lucky! I... *cough*... caught that potent poison!~
@3069 = ~That is clearly evident.~
@3070 = ~Don't worry! I’ll heal you.~
@3071 = ~If you call that luck, I never want to know what misfortune looks like to you.~
@3072 = ~Splendid! Everything turned out well.~
@3073 = ~What are you talking about?~
@3074 = ~I was hit by the poison, but one of the arrows got lodged in my tunic. The tip's still laced with it.~
@3075 = ~Couldn’t have worked out better!~
@3076 = ~Poisoned and still clinging to your mission. You Eldathyn really are stubborn.~
@3077 = ~That arrow may point us straight to the bastard responsible.~
@3078 = ~Meaning?~
@3079 = ~With the poison in hand, we can study it! Well... not me anymore. Eldath's still waters await me. I can feel her pull already... So the task falls to you now!~
@3080 = ~You must... must bring this arrow, poison and all, to Most Exalted Fallskeeper Alatoasz Berendim, high priest of my order, in Duskwood Dell. He’ll know how to proceed.~
@3081 = ~That's a very long title your high priest is holding.~
@3082 = ~You have my word. I’ll take it to him.~
@3083 = ~The Fallskeeper will know, and someone will pay for what’s been done to you.~
@3084 = ~If it helps end this madness, I’ll do it.~
@3085 = ~What about you? I thought you would be the one to work with me!~
@3086 = ~I’ve had enough. I want nothing more to do with this.~
@3087 = ~Titles mean little to him, truly. But among our order, it honors his wisdom and years of service. Behind it stands a man of rare peace and purpose—you’ll see.~
@3088 = ~What about you?~
@3089 = ~Very well. Tell me where this place is.~
@3090 = ~You need not worry about me. My path ends here, as a river eventually flows into the vast sea and is lost within it. You must carry on the task and go to Duskwood Dell!~
@3091 = ~I don't know. I don't want to be part of this anymore.~
@3092 = ~The path has already taken you in, even if you step away. Please... if not for me, then for those who may yet be spared. I can do no more. But you still can. Go to Duskwood Dell.~
@3093 = ~Duskwood Dell is the heart of my faith—not just in Amn, but across all of Faerûn. It is there that the trail of poison must be followed. My temple lies hidden within the Snakewood. It is difficult to find under normal circumstances... but I shall tell you how to reach it.~
@3094 = ~And I almost forgot—our enemy, in his vanity, revealed his true face! Tell Alatoasz that I was poisoned by a Malagent... he will know what that means.~
@3095 = ~No more words... Let this forest cradle my breath, and her breeze carry me to the still waters...~
@3096 = ~He was so kind... I wish we could have done more.~
@3097 = ~Your path ends in stillness, as all must. May your soul merge with the quiet waters you served so faithfully.~
@3098 = ~How touching. The weak always love to pretend their end has meaning.~
@3099 = ~Rest now, priest of Eldath. The forest will remember you, as will we. May your spirit find stillness.~
@3100 = ~You exit the stage with naught but a whisper and a breeze... A fitting end for one who worshipped silence.~
@3101 = ~Another corpse in the dirt. You flesh-born mourn too easily. At least he didn’t scream—it makes disposal so much simpler.~
@3102 = ~Oh no... That’s just awful. I mean, peaceful and all, but still awful. Do you think his goddess really takes him somewhere?~
@3103 = ~You chose your place well, priest. A quiet end beneath ancient boughs... May your spirit drift with the wind, far from this poisoned world.~
@3104 = ~Death is like a bad case of the trots—you never feel it comin’ till it’s too late and halfway down your trousers.~
@3105 = ~Go gently, brother. The leaves shall whisper your name, and the wind shall carry your breath into the endless cycle.~
@3106 = ~He dies with purpose—and in faith. May his goddess receive him.~
@3107 = ~I honor your devotion. Rest now, servant of Eldath—your sacrifice shall be remembered.~
@3108 = ~You gave everything for your faith... I hope your goddess grants you peace, truly. The world could use more like you.~
@3109 = ~He was a good man, Boo agrees! May the forest cradle him gently... and may the poisoner feel my righteous fury soon!~
@3110 = ~Peace and poison—a charming combination. I’m sure his goddess approves of the irony.~
@3111 = ~An idealist bleeds out in the dirt, babbling about peace. Let the worms have him—perhaps they’ll be inspired to pacifism.~
@3112 = ~If I ever die like that—flat on me back in a pile o’ birdshite, starin’ up at leaves—ye’d best throw me on a pyre quick, else I’ll rise from the grave, ‘fore the shame kills me twice!~
@3113 = ~Peace... finally...~
@3114 = ~Greetings, stranger. A fine place to conduct business out here in the wilds, isn't it? Plenty of mushrooms around—just be careful not to pick the poisonous ones.~
@3115 = ~No need to pretend, priest. My contacts in Athkatla told me you were coming.~ [STHMA04]
@3116 = ~That's good! Then you have brought the poison I so desire?~
@3117 = ~I have! And you’ll be tasting it soon enough!~
@3118 = ~What do you mean...~
@3119 = ~How stupid do you think I am, Eldathyn? You believe I can’t see through your scheming? That I wouldn’t notice those brutes hiding among the trees?~
@3120 = ~You meant to ambush me, but instead I’ve turned the trap on you. Wadal, my loyal servant?~
@3121 = ~Yesss, massster?~
@3122 = ~Take the special arrow I prepared. Fire it at that miserable peace-craver.~
@3123 = ~With eassse... Wadal never misssesss.~
@3124 = ~<CHARNAME>! To me!~
@3125 = ~Your <CHARNAME> won’t save you. You’ll get the poison you desire, oh yes! Right in your heart!~
@3126 = ~This should be the place. Please wait here—I’ll go ahead and try to negotiate. Only intervene if things go poorly.~
@3127 = ~Hello again, <CHARNAME>. Shall we depart to Toadstool Hollow?~
@3128 = ~Sure! Let’s go.~
@3129 = ~Not just yet. I need a little more time.~
@3130 = ~Good to see you again! Were you able to make Skann Delth talk? Do you know where he’s meeting the poison supplier?~
@3131 = ~Yes, I managed to get the information. I’ve got a document that mentions the location.~
@3132 = ~No, I haven’t found anything yet.~
@3133 = ~Excellent. Let me take a look...~
@3134 = ~Toadstool Hollow? I know this place. Secluded, rarely visited—an ideal location for a meeting like this. There’s only one path forward now: We go there and see whether the mysterious poisoner reveals himself. Shall we depart?~
@3135 = ~Excellent! The journey shouldn't take too long from here.~
@3136 = ~Farewell, my dear Ilmaterian friend, thank you again for your hospitality within these sacred halls.~
@3137 = ~Farewell, priest of the Hidden Goddess. May Ilmater’s blessings go with you as well.~
@3138 = ~Then let us be on our way.~
@3139 = ~Then I shall remain here and wait for you.~
@3140 = ~Greetings, <CHARNAME>. Forgive me for addressing you by name, but I have observed you for a while and I've finally decided to approach you. I may have need of your help.~
@3141 = ~You have my attention. What sort of help do you require?~
@3142 = ~Gladly—if the pay is right.~
@3143 = ~I don’t appreciate being spied on.~
@3144 = ~Find someone else for your troubles.~
@3145 = ~I meant no offense. In times such as these, caution is survival. May I speak to you of what I have to offer?~
@3146 = ~Tell me what troubles you.~
@3147 = ~What is it you want?~
@3148 = ~I'll listen—if the pay is right.~
@3149 = ~Allow me to introduce myself. I am Merethan, devoted servant of Eldath, the goddess of peace and groves.~
@3150 = ~Eldath’s servants are rare in times like these. I hope his words carry more than peaceful pleasantries.~
@3151 = ~An Eldathyn! A gentle presence in a world far too fond of thunder.~
@3152 = ~Well met, Merethan. What can I do for you?~
@3153 = ~It’s an honor to meet a servant of Eldath. What brings you to me?~
@3154 = ~You know who I am. But I don’t yet know your purpose here, so let’s hear what you want from me.~
@3155 = ~Eldath? Never heard of her before.~
@3156 = ~My goddess is the protector of peace, still waters, and quiet places. She teaches us to heal and do no harm. In her name, I require your help. Allow me to explain.~
@3157 = ~Not long ago, you crossed paths with a poisoned man—Renfeld, if I recall correctly. You brought him here to Athkatla, badly poisoned.~
@3158 = ~I do not know where he is now, nor how he fares. What I do know, however, is that the toxin which struck him down is cause for grave concern.~
@3159 = ~Most types of poison can be cured—or at least delayed—with clerical spells or common antidotes. But none of them worked on poor Renfeld. Whatever was used on him resists all attempts to purge it. And there’s even more to worry about.~
@3160 = ~The truly troubling part is: This wasn’t the first time this kind of poison has been used—immune to all magic, beyond any known cure. Such occurrences are becoming disturbingly frequent.~
@3161 = ~To be undone by a kiss of venom no prayer can touch... such is the cruelty of a world that sings its sorrow in silence.~
@3162 = ~I’ve studied healing prayers, but... I’ve never heard of anything they couldn’t touch. This must be something truly terrifying.~
@3163 = ~How quaint. Natha elg'cahl phor jal elg'cahlen: A poison above all poisons.~
@3164 = ~An incurable poison? That can't be. I know there is a cure. There always is.~
@3165 = ~This toxin is a crime against life itself. It's not as cutting down a tree, but corruption of all the water that runs under a forest.~
@3166 = ~By the grace of Arvoreen, we must not allow such vile poison to take root! Whoever crafts such wickedness must be held to account.~
@3167 = ~No matter what, poison is always a coward’s weapon.~
@3168 = ~If there is a power behind this plague of venom, then it must be cast down, for the sake of all decent folk.~
@3169 = ~As always, those who suffer most are the ones without coin. No bodyguards. No tasters. Just trust in their water—and death in their cups.~
@3170 = ~A poison beyond the reach of your pitiful prayers? Perhaps your gods are simply not listening.~
@3171 = ~Even the calmest waters ripple when danger approaches. By the will of the Church of Eldath, I have been tasked to uncover the secret behind this poison.~
@3172 = ~I'm curious. Tell me more.~
@3173 = ~That's horrifying! Who could be responsible for this?~
@3174 = ~If someone’s behind this, they’ll regret it soon enough.~
@3175 = ~Perfect poison for someone with a dagger and dark intentions!~
@3176 = ~Sounds useful, this toxin.~
@3177 = ~I initially suspected that one of Faerûn’s more malevolent groups had devised this terrible poison. But my search uncovered something troubling: The poison has been used by unrelated factions, with no alliance or shared interest between them. No shared ambition—only the same deadly means.~
@3178 = ~That can only mean a different power is behind this—one that acts on his own, working in the shadows. Someone who delights in the death this poison leaves behind.~
@3179 = ~Silent but violent... This stuff’s like flatulence at a turnip banquet: You don’t know who did it, but someone’s definitely going to suffer.~
@3180 = ~So you want me to face this poison-maker?~
@3181 = ~And just how are we meant to find this mysterious mastermind?~
@3182 = ~Sounds like you have a task in mind for me...~
@3183 = ~Whatever this is, it’s not my problem. Find someone else.~
@3184 = ~It will be difficult to find the real perpetrator. We cannot strike at shadows. We must clear the overgrowth gently, one branch at a time, until the path to the poison reveals itself.~
@3185 = ~I’ve already tried to make contact with someone who might lead us to the one behind all this. There's a shady figure here in the slums of Athkatla who claims he can procure rare poisons. I pretended to be a potential buyer. Unfortunately, I couldn’t get him to reveal the whereabouts of his supplier. He grew wary—and resentful.~
@3186 = ~I seem to lack the persuasive skills required in such dealings. You, however, may prove more capable in such matters.~
@3187 = ~You worship peace, but send others to do your bidding when matters grow inconvenient?~
@3188 = ~Persuasion, eh? Nothing persuades better than a broken nose and a few missing teeth.~
@3189 = ~So even the faithful of the gentle goddess know when to call upon sharper tongues.~
@3190 = ~I ask you to seek out a poison dealer named Skann Delth in the slums of Athkatla. He is too dim-witted to brew the poisons himself. He has to get them from someone else. If you discover the source of his supply, I ask you to accompany me to confront the one behind it all.~
@3191 = ~Fine, I can do that.~
@3192 = ~What’s in it for me?~
@3193 = ~No, I won’t do it.~
@3194 = ~I do not expect you to act without reward. Gold means little to those of my faith, but I can offer you a number of soothing potions should you agree to assist me in this matter.~
@3195 = ~Very well. I'm in.~
@3196 = ~I'll help you.~
@3197 = ~No, I’m not doing this.~
@3198 = ~Are you certain you won’t help me?~
@3199 = ~All right, I’ll help you.~
@3200 = ~I won’t help you.~
@3201 = ~Excellent! Skann Delth usually lingers on the roof of the Copper Coronet, boasting about his brews. Most of them are of little use; tricks and tinctures for fools. You should insist you're looking for something truly dangerous. Try to find out where he gets his poison from.~
@3202 = ~I will wait for you at the temple of Ilmater in the Slums. His priests offer me shelter whenever I need it. Find me there once you’ve learned anything—so we know where to continue the search for the source of this mysterious poison.~
@3203 = ~That is unfortunate. Are you sure you don't want to help me?~
@3204 = ~Alright, I will try help you.~
@3205 = ~Yes, I'm sure. Find someone else.~
@3206 = ~Alright, I shall have to seek help elsewhere.~
@3207 = ~Muscles? Nay! But behold—BOO! The fury of righteousness!~
